ein [GP], nucleoprotein [NP], or RNA-dependent RNA polymerase [L]) in cell culture, as well as in mice and ferrets, by generating recombinant viruses (based on an early West African EBOV strain) each carrying one of these mutations. The NP and L mutations appear to decrease virulence, whereas the GP mutation slightly increases virulence but mainly impacts viral tropism. Our results show that these single mutations can impact EBOV virulence in animals and have implications for the rational design of efficacious antiviral therapies against these infections.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Wong, Gary", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "He, Shihua", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leung, Anders", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cao, Wenguang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bi, Yuhai", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhang, Zirui", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhu, Wenjun", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wang, Liang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhao, Yuhui", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cheng, Keding", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Liu, Di", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Liu, Wenjun", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kobasa, Darwyn", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gao, George F.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Qiu, Xiangguo", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/2a9f651a4067cbb33b2e1ff5f1f0159d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/6ca41a06f09aff6fdff0617bf147e8a8bf49499af035e20e89c12ad8478a83f2", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/2HLGLT7Y", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/2HLGLT7Y", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/f2873c116ce826094da2ca408c8ca26c!/b320065-322631", "re